reviews.text:
The food was incredible!
The service seemed a little disconnected,
perhaps an off night, but just a little disjointed, and items were coming out oddly timed,

The food however‚Ä¶.

Absolutely delicious!

I eat a lot of Indian cuisine, and I mean a lot.
I have eaten at Indian restaurants all over the country, and this place, had the best Korma of anywhere I have been.
The food was seriously delicious, I cannot recommend it enough.
Get there a little earlier than you normally would as it does get busy quickly and there‚Äôs not a lot of seating.

This is what I would consider a hole in the wall place, and I mean that in all positive aspects. It's small and tucked away in a little strip mall, but WOW, great food. My wife ordered the butter chicken and said it was the best she'd ever had. The presentation of the entrees is very creative and artistic. Love that! The wait staff were very attentive and kind. And for a tiny little space, the owners have done a great job decorating and creating an authentic cultural environment. We'll definitely be coming back, and highly suggest you give it a shot too. You won't be disappointed.

The food was scrumptious, absolutely great service and really liked how the owners introduced themselves and chatted with our group. The experience felt very personalized. We had ordered jeera drink, and mango mule. Fantastic refreshers for a summer day! For appetizers we had dhaaba chicken kabab and veg cheese kebabs. The kebabs were very tender, great presentation and tasted great. Even the chutneys were so flavorful. For entrees we had chole bhature, malai kofta, chicken chettinad. The chole were good though could have been better. Missed that dhaba style flavor. Chicken chettinad was also very tasty. The star dish for our group was the malai kofta! Stunning texture and flavor. Not sweet but the perfect balance of spices. We also tried dahi bhalla. The bhalla was slightly crumbly but the overall flavors were delicious. We also tried the kulfi and shahi tukda for dessert. Loved both. Ordered the shahi tukda twice, that‚Äôs how much we liked it.
Overall the experience was wonderful, great food, amazing service, very polite hosts. We went home with our tummies and heart full! üòá
This place is great! My wife and I love the lunch buffet. Everything I've had here has been incredibly good, especially the garlic naan. The atmosphere is very nice and the people are kind.

detailedReviews.author: Parth Patel
detailedReviews.text:
A Hidden Gem in SLC ‚Äì Must Visit for Food Lovers!
If you're in Salt Lake City and craving authentic, mouth-watering Indian food, look no further than SLC Dhaba. The atmosphere is warm and inviting, but it's the food that steals the show.
I highly recommend the Fish Amritsari ‚Äì it was absolutely delicious! The crispy batter, perfectly spiced fish, and that tangy dip ‚Äì every bite was a burst of flavor. Honestly, it‚Äôs one of the best I‚Äôve had outside of India.

The only place serving Authentic food in salt lake. Every food item was served with care, it was like sitting in a restaurant in India - if you know what I mean :) try all items in the menu and don‚Äôt miss the Kukfi!
Congrats to Deepak and team super friendly people!

detailedReviews.author: Vivian Bentley
detailedReviews.text: The chole bhature was divine! So delicious. The Dahl and pakora were also great, but the star of the show was the chole bhature. We will definitely be back for more, and will recommend to our friends and family. The service was really fast and friendly. My water glass was never empty.

detailedReviews.author: Vicky Atwood
detailedReviews.text: Amazing food, can't wait to come back

detailedReviews.author: Manav Shroff
detailedReviews.text: Best Indian food in Utah

detailedReviews.author: Ravishankar Balou
detailedReviews.text:
Heard by word of mouth and we were here on a weekday for dinner. Nice ambience and the quality of food is very good. Paneer Tikka was fresh, soft and delicious, channa masala was at the right spicy and well made. Dal Makhani was just yummy and creamy.

The home made kulfi was the ultimatum.

detailedReviews.author: Tyler Hamilton
detailedReviews.text: Just delicious. Flavor and texture were spot on. I will definitely be recommending in the future.

detailedReviews.author: Case Hamilton
detailedReviews.text: The food here is absolutely amazing. The servers are super kind and the owner is wonderful. It was great food with a huge menu.

detailedReviews.author: Venkatraman Srikanth
detailedReviews.text:
Exceptional! A hidden gem in SLC, truly authentic and tasty Indian food.

Service was extremely fast too. We had the Shahi Paneer, Yellow dal, and Malai kofta. We'll definitely be back!

detailedReviews.author: Kevin Anson
detailedReviews.text:
SLC Dhaba is hands down one of the best spots for authentic North Indian food in Salt Lake! The chicken tikka masala and butter chicken are both amazing, super flavorful and comforting, and their cheese garlic naan is the perfect side to soak it all up.

The real winner though is their seekh kebabs‚Äîjuicy, smoky, and full of flavor. Definitely try their Dhaba Special Kebab, which is kind of like a Kathi roll‚Äîit‚Äôs unique and sooo good.

Portions are generous, staff is friendly, and the food always hits the spot. If you‚Äôre craving Indian food, this is the place.

detailedReviews.author: Nicole Campolucci
detailedReviews.text: I was finally able to try this restaurant tonight and am so happy I did! Service was great‚Ä¶friendly without being overbearing (I believe our server is one of the owners). The food was absolutely delicious and incredibly flavorful as Indian food should be. We had the monthly appetizer special which was so unique (fried spinach leaves topped with chickpeas, yogurt, and a couple of chutneys) and like nothing I have ever had before. The chicken saag, butter chicken, and garlic naan were all also very good. I can‚Äôt wait to go back and am grateful I live nearby!

detailedReviews.author: Hailey Bressard
detailedReviews.text: Love this place! The service was great and it was fun to learn about the story of the restaurant. The food was AMAZING and we tried many different dishes. We got the butter chicken, chicken saag, garlic naan, and some fried spinach dish that we forgot the name of. It was all so good and we left full and happy! They also have many gluten free options which is great!

detailedReviews.author: Justin Hershey
detailedReviews.text: This place is great! My wife and I love the lunch buffet. Everything I've had here has been incredibly good, especially the garlic naan. The atmosphere is very nice and the people are kind.

detailedReviews.author: John Poulos
detailedReviews.text: We went there on Saturday night. My complaint is about the two waitresses working here. They stand in the corner, look at you and gossip, unfriendly and won‚Äôt tell you if the kitchen has closed for orders or anything. Just kept filling our waters. We wanted to order more and we were not full if only we knew about last orders. The waitresses are not doing their job well. Manager guy was okay but we tried to make a conversation with him and he didnt seem to care to connect with us at all. Super weird for a new business to be so unfriendly.

detailedReviews.author: abid ali
detailedReviews.text: Hands down the best food and ambience. Must try Dahi Balla.

detailedReviews.author: Mohammed Abdul Rafe
detailedReviews.text: I would definitely recommend this place. Delicious

detailedReviews.author: Ashwarya Jage

detailedReviews.text: Fantastic Food and Service!

detailedReviews.author: Robert Dority
detailedReviews.text: Filled water glasses with room temperature water. Had to ask for ice. Service was slow for not being very busy. Food was all right, but nothing to write home about.

detailedReviews.author: Rohit Misri
detailedReviews.text: had an amazing brunch at SLC Dhaba! The food is pure authentic North Indian taste‚Äîit instantly brought me back to India. We‚Äôve really been missing this kind of food in Salt Lake City, so thank you for bringing such an authentic experience here. The service was excellent, and the staff were warm and welcoming. Highly recommend for anyone craving real Indian flavors!

detailedReviews.author: Jai Ganesh
detailedReviews.text: Fooled by the reviews. The appetizer was salty. Bhatura was nothing like the picture and was so small and thick. Naan was thick and not properly cooked. Chana masala was not tasty. They also mixed up the Garlic Naan and the roti order, so I paid the garlic naan price for roti. The taste was not anywhere close to a dhaba and is expensive. May be they have the non veg tasting better but I highly doubt it. Really disappointed.

detailedReviews.author: Tyler Dodge

detailedReviews.text: The customer service could not be any better! They make the experience so great from the beginning! Would highly recommend 100%!!

detailedReviews.author: Manmeet Kaur

Omg! Such amazing food!
We tried their samosa chaat, kebab, tandoori wings and Amritsar fish! Everything just hit the right spots! It was all so tasty, just like India. Amazing service. Would definitely visit again.

detailedReviews.author: Shawn Kory Stevens
detailedReviews.text: Unreal. So good

detailedReviews.author: Cris Payne
detailedReviews.text: Wonderful food, wonderful atmosphere, and wonderful service. Food is authentic, rich in taste, and ample portions. Deepak, the owner, is a great gentlemen, and you can tell, takes great pride in his restaurant.I will definitely be coming back. The high reviews are well deserved.

detailedReviews.text: 1st time coming to this new restaurant looked up new places around me and came to try a local place, cute little atmosphere and restaurant very nice people and good service very attentive and met the owner and asked about the restaurant name and heard the backstory which was super cool! Loved it and will come back!

detailedReviews.author: Puja Sah
detailedReviews.text: Authentic flavors, cozy ambiance, and great service. The butter chicken was rich and flavorful, and the naan was perfectly crispy. Highly recommend for anyone craving a true taste .

detailedReviews.author: Priyanka Lekurwale
detailedReviews.text: Excellent Indian food.

detailedReviews.author: toni harbour
detailedReviews.text: Super friendly, unique flavors, strong delicious spices. It feels good to go to dinner here! The masala tea is the best!

detailedReviews.author: Val Johnson
detailedReviews.text: We enjoyed every bite!  Authentic and very flavorful.  Servers were attentive, friendly and gave us great menu suggestions as it was our first time.  They have so many choices we will definitely be back.  Looking forward to trying their buffet as well.  Highly recommend!

detailedReviews.author: Mahfuzur Jony
detailedReviews.text: Went there seeing 4.9 rating, however, I don‚Äôt think the rating should be that high as a native south Asian. Buffet doesn‚Äôt have any mutton, samosa, chicken tikka masala. Buffet items are quite limited. Won‚Äôt be back.

detailedReviews.text: The food was very delicious and took time because they make it fresh from scratch but definitely worth the wait!

detailedReviews.author: Katie MacMillan
detailedReviews.text:
MUST TRY! Amazing food, amazing service, amazing vibe.

Started with the Dhaba kebab special ‚Äî WOW! Very unique and an instant favorite. The samosas were amazing as well. Sauces were 10/10.

For our entrees we had the lamb korma, lamb saag, and lamb Rogan curry and everything was incredible. Different flavor from Indian places I‚Äôve had but in all the right ways; very flavorful and fresh.

We will be back!

detailedReviews.author: Emma Langford
detailedReviews.text: Great lunch buffet!

detailedReviews.author: Tyler Crump
detailedReviews.text: Food was fantastic. Service was great!
